      <h5 style="font-size:16px"><span class="w3-tag w3-wide w3-grey w3-text-white"><strong>BOTS IN TOP TWEETERS</strong></span></h5>
      <p class="w3-text-grey">When I carefully compared the other data, I found that these accounts all had very high overall bot scores because they had a lot of fake followers, while accounts like real people had spammer scores, self declared and other scores below 1. This seems to indicate that people are more likely to believe tweets from accounts with a high number of followers on the #IoT topic.
        <br><br><strong style="color:#CD5C5C">Is it possible that with such a highly professional topic, there is no way for what a normal person says to be visible to others?</strong>
